    &lt;Title&gt;Surgical staff&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Im writing this hoping the staff in the general surgical department see and know its a big thank you.I recently came for a minor operation but the aneastatist immediatly put me at ease she was amazing throughout an i hope she knows how lovely she really  was, i have a degenerative muscle disease meaning i wear an orthotic brace around my arm and shoulder. She took time to understand what it does for me an could probably see i was very nervous about having to take it off during surgery, which she straight away said i could keep it on and she'd sort it all out etc. She was genuinly caring and compassionate and amzing at her job and i was very thankful to have her looking after me throughout even after in the recovery room making sure i had everything i needed as i need alot more painkillers than others due to my tolerance, an she was spot on.In the recovery room afterwards there were two lovely nurses one pretending to be harry Potter but it cheered me right up anyway,  i work for the nhs on a ward and know staff are rushed and tired etc so things arent always perfect but these nurses were born for that job they showed how it should be done. She made sure i wasn't  in pain she gave me a wet cloth for my forehead a warm towel for my stomach and stroked my hair it was like having your nanna look after you but in the best way just caring and compassionate. Thank you to everyone in the surgical department you were all  absolutely  cracking at your jobs.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
